# EAS Build uploads the whole git repo by default, then runs from this
# project (apps/mobile/). The monorepo's pnpm-workspace.yaml excludes
# apps/mobile, which trips up EAS's default `pnpm install --frozen-lockfile`
# (installs nothing for mobile because it isn't in the workspace).
#
# We force EAS to treat apps/mobile as a STANDALONE pnpm project by:
#   1. excluding the workspace config files from upload (this file), and
#   2. providing an `eas-build-pre-install` script in package.json that
#      runs `pnpm install --ignore-workspace`.
#
# Paths are relative to project root (apps/mobile/). `../../` = monorepo root.
# We KEEP packages/shared because metro.config.js bundles its source.
../../pnpm-workspace.yaml
../../pnpm-lock.yaml
../backend
../frontend
